@startuml Graph Layer Edge Types
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam defaultFontSize 11

title Graph Layer — Edge Types & Traversal Examples

graph "Knowledge Graph" as G {

    node "session_20260518" as s1
    node "task_fix_auth" as t1
    node "bug_crash_login" as b1
    node "commit_abc123" as c1
    node "src/auth.ts" as f1
    node "src/lib/jwt.ts" as f2
    node "REQ-001" as r1
    node "knowledge_jwt_best" as k1

    s1 -[bold,#Blue]-> t1 : same_session
    s1 -[bold,#Blue]-> b1 : same_session
    t1 -[bold,#Red]-> b1 : fixed_by
    t1 -[bold,#Green]-> c1 : implements
    c1 -[bold,#Orange]-> f1 : modifies
    f1 -[bold,#Purple]-> f2 : imports
    f1 -[#Gray]-> r1 : implements
    t1 -[#Teal]-> k1 : depends_on
}

legend right
    |= Edge Type |= Color |= Meaning |
    | same_session | <#Blue> | Created in same session |
    | fixed_by | <#Red> | Bug fix chain |
    | implements | <#Green> | Code fulfills requirement |
    | modifies | <#Orange> | Commit changes file |
    | imports | <#Purple> | Code dependency |
    | depends_on | <#Teal> | Task prerequisite |
    | parent_dir | <#Gray> | File in directory |
end legend

note bottom of G
  **Traversal examples:**
  • session → all tasks → all fixes (chain)
  • bug → who fixed it → what commit → what files
  • file → who imports it → reverse dependency
  • requirement → all implementing code
end note

@enduml
